annotationA: ATP binding cassette subfamily B member 7 (ABCB7) is a transporter that likely dimerizes to form a functional transporter. ABCB7 may act in the mitochondria to transport substrates necessary for the maturation of ICS proteins, which are involved in iron homeostasis
annotationB: Heat shock protein cognate 20 (Hsc20) is a mitochondrial chaperone that facilitates iron sulfur cluster assembly or transfer from IscU to other scaffold proteins. Hsc20 is required for larval growth and cellular iron sensing
